ht one is crucial, since it could significantly impact your business. This is because it allows your customers to use digital payments like credit and debit cards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Many small businesses owners are still struggling to find out the best way to accept customers\u2019 money. Although the process looks simple due to the many payment options in the payments industry, for many businesses, it is not. This is because of data breaches, hackers, among many other things. The best way to go about it is to <a href=\"https:\/\/uhurunetwork.com\/payment-gateways-and-how-to-choose-the-right-one-for-your-business\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">choose a payment gateway<\/a> that is trustworthy and secure. It will help to protect your business against any potential hacks and frauds.<br>In this article, you will learn how payment processors work, why you need them and how to pick the right one for your business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-is-a-payment-processor-and-how-does-it-work\"><\/span>What is a Payment Processor, and How Does It Work?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many people confuse between a payment processor and a payment gateway. They sound similar, but they are not. A payment gateway is a tool that sends payments between your bank and the customer\u2019s bank. On the other hand, a payment processor is a firm or company that transfers money from your customer\u2019s bank to your bank account.<br>The processor ensures that the money is securely transferred into your account. This is how it works to ensure the transactions happen successfully.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 The payment processor verifies the billing information of the customer<br>\u2022 It ensures the correct amount of money is available, and the funds for each payment are authenticated.<br>\u2022 Payment requests are approved, and orders confirmation digits are sent<br>\u2022 Finally, it approves the transaction and sends the money to the merchant\u2019s account before it is deposited into your bank account.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are three players involved in the financial transaction to make the whole process successful and secure.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"players-involved-in-financial-transaction\"><\/span>Players Involved in Financial Transaction<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the digital payment system, there are players involved in the processing of transactions. They include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 The Merchant: In the payments industry, you need a merchant to apply the credit or debit card payment method on your website. This is usually the bank that accepts your customer\u2019s payments on your behalf. Also known as the merchant bank or acquirer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Customer: Your customers also need to be present to make the payments solution possible. The bank issues customers credit or debit cards they can use to purchase items in your business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Technology: Between the merchant and the customer, two types of technologies are involved in the digital payment system. That is the payment gateway and payment processor, which does most of the work. It works with the bank, sends you billing information, and moves transactions via a processing network.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/players-involved-in-a-financial-transaction-for-payment-processors.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1072\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/players-involved-in-a-financial-transaction-for-payment-processors.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/players-involved-in-a-financial-transaction-for-payment-processors-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/players-involved-in-a-financial-transaction-for-payment-processors-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"factors-to-consider-when-selecting-a-payment-processor\"><\/span>Factors to Consider When Selecting a Payment Processor<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Costs Should Be As Low As Possible<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking at the cost the payment processor is offering is very crucial. It is important to keep costs as low as possible. Some of the costs involved in digital payments are;<br>\u2022 Interchange \u2013 What the customer\u2019s bank deducts<br>\u2022 Markup \u2013 percentage taken by the merchant bank<br>\u2022 Assessment \u2013 pre-negotiation charges<br>\u2022 Possessing fee \u2013 fee deducted by the payment processor<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Multiple Payment Options Will Improve the Business<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a business owner, you should have multiple digital payments solution for your customers. This will allow you to reach all customers as they will pay with their preferred payment method. It also means you should choose a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bigcommerce.com\/ecommerce-answers\/how-choose-payment-processor\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">payment processor<\/a> that offers you this freedom. If the customer does not want to pay by credit card, they should have the option to use bank transfer or debit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Secure Your Business against Hackers<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your financial transaction information is crucial, and this is why you should pick a secure payment processor. Ensure that the processor you are using has fraud detection tools and all your transaction information will be encrypted. This will also help your customers feel secure when purchasing products from your stores.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Choose a Convenient Payment Processor<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A convenient payment processor will make everything effortless for you and your customers. Try to avoid complicated payments solution that might make your customers give up in the buying process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Look At the Speed of Money Transfer<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Selling is not the only important thing in a business. You also have to ensure that digital payments methods offer fast transactions. This means that the payment processor you are using should also be efficient and fast. It will increase customer satisfaction and make the business prosper quickly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Go Through the Fee and Service Agreements<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before agreeing to partner with a payment processor, it is important to look at their agreements. Look at what they expect from you and if you can comply with that. The fee agreement may be based on business sales, transactions, and revenue consistency.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"benefits-of-having-a-payment-processor\"><\/span>Benefits of Having a Payment Processor<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Small business owners can benefit greatly from using a payment processor. The digital payment system comes with plenty of advantages, which include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Quick Payments\u2013Payment processors can complete various transactions quickly, which will boost customer experience and satisfaction.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/business-account\/#:~:text=Transaction%20security%20%2D%20Rest%20assured%20that%20every%20transaction%20is%20safe%20from%20fraudsters%20and%20hackers.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Secure Transactions<\/a>\u2013 In the payments industry, security is one of the most crucial things to be looked at. Payment processors allow businesses to have their data transferred safely and securely.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 More Customers\u2013 With a payment processor, you can reach customers from all parts of the world. It does not limit you to only customers from within your region.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Convenience\u2013 Having a payment gateway or processor is like having your store open 24\/7. This allows you to make money even when you sleep.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"final-words\"><\/span>Final Words<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Digital payments are one thing online business owners can use to make the buying process fast and easy for customers. But there is another thing they should consider, which is a payment processor as it allows financial transactions to flow smoothly. Above are a few things you can look at before using one.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction Whether you are starting or growing your business, payment processors will come in handy; and choosing the right one is crucial, since it could significantly impact your business. This is because it allows your customers to use digital payments like credit and debit cards. Many small businesses owners are still struggling to find out [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":408,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16,14,20],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/338"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=338"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/338\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1073,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/338\/revisions\/1073"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/408"}]